review_blob:
Bottle from Systembolaget, Sweden.
Short dark brown head. Very dark color. 
Coconut aroma and cinnemon that together resembles "Cocosbollar".
Chocolate rich full bodied taste with sweetness and strong alcohol and coffey.
beer_name: West Coast Bryggeri / All In Brewing Handshake

review_blob: Draught at Monks cafe Wallingatan. Lasting beige head. Solid amber color. Nice fruity hop aroma with a bit caramell. Smooth hoppy taste and a firm bitterness to balanced a firm malty taste.
Draught at Monks cafe Wallingatan. Short head. Clowdy solid yellow color. Mild pommegranate aroma with a small lactic acidity. Mild lactic taste and small fruitiness.
Lasting white head. Clear solid golden color. No sparkle. Lacking hop aroma for an Ipa. Hard bitterness and low body.
beer_name: Brutal Brewing The Wonder of IPA

review_blob: Cask at Akkurat Stockholm. Lasting light brown head. Malty light roasted aroma. Sweet malty brown malt taste. Medium body and balanced bitterness.
Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Fresh ripe tropical apricot aroma. Fresh fruity light acidity making it very nice and refreshing. Light body.
Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Semi lasting off white head. Clowdy golden color. Small clean malty aroma. Sweet malty taste with a balanced bitterness. Big body.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Hoppy Lager

review_blob: Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Nice big white head. Opaque yellow color. Spicy hop aroma. Sweet malty taste and low bitterness.
Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Malty aroma and a bit tired hop. Sweet malty taste with a spicy bitterness.

Can from Systembolaget, Sweden.
Big solid brown head. Very dark brown color beer..Huge aroma from coconutand a bit vanilla. Smooth taste from coconut and mild chocolate. Low bitterness and a medium body. Some residual sweetness.
beer_name: Oskar Blues / Shamrock Death By Coconut

review_blob: Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Big and lasting beige head. Clowdy amber color. Big complex piny hop aroma with a very nice caramell aroma. Equally nice malty taste from long boiled wort to give a nice roasted /smoked taste. Big bitterness for a scottish ale but balance well with all other taste.
beer_name: Birra del Borgo / BrewDog ReAle in Kilt

review_blob:
Can from systembolaget, Sweden.
Semi lasting white head. Opaque solid yellow color. Medium citrus hop aroma. Citrus hop taste and small to medium bitterness. No sweetness.

Bottle from systembolaget, Sweden.
Lasting dark grey head. Clear very nice red-amber color.
Strange aroma from celery and root vegetables.
Mild taste from light dark malts. Low bitterness but alcohole clearly present.
Medium body.
Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Semi lasting White head. Opaque solid amber color. Big caramell and hoppy aroma. Sweet caramell taste blended with a fruity hop taste. Abnit sweet taste.

Draught at Stringfellows pub, Stockholm. Light opaque golden color. Lasting white fluffy head. Fresh citrus hop aroma. Mild session ale with fresh hop taste and low bitterness. Medium body and no residual sweetness.

Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Medium lasting off white head. Light opaque golden color. Phenolic and murcy apple aroma. Tired caramell taste that is almost a bit fishy. Low bitterness and big body.
Bottle from systembolaget sweden. Big and lasting light brown head. Clear red brown color. Nice phenolic and caramell aroma. Sweet malty taste with a small caramell tuch and a big body.
beer_name: Dieu du Ciel Rigor Mortis Abt

review_blob:
Draught at the Tegel airport, Berlin.
Fine white head. Clear solid yellow color. Weak DMS aroma. Malty taste and low sweetness. Medium body and low bitterness.

Bottle sampled at Thomas W, Thanks.
Short head. Clowdy brown color. Huge spicy aroma almost spiced by a Jgermeister. The taste is also spicy with a medium bitternes.

Big and fluffy white head. Opaque golden color and without any bubles in the glas. Mild malty aroma from Wiener and pilsner malts. Light roasted malty taste and some hop taste. Medium body and some residual sweetness.

Bottle from Vagabund Brauerei, Berlin.
Tiny off white head. Clear golden color. Woody and a small stable aroma followed by a distinct lactic aciduty. Fresh lactic taste with mooth maltiness No sweetness and a slim body.

Dr aught at the brewery.
No head. Opaque golden color. Mild hoppy aroma for a DIPA with a touch of sawdust plate. Fresh and fruity hop taste. Low bitterness for a DIPA. Well fermented to give a low residual sweetness. Medium body.

Dr aught at the brewpub. Small lingering beige head. Almost clear red- amber color. Mild and fruity aroma from red currants leaves. Fruity and full bodied beer. Nicely balanced and some residual sweetness.
Draught at the brewpub. Lasting white head. Clear solid golden color. An aroma of band aid / Hospital desinfectant. Perculiar taste from strawberry leaves.

Draught at the brewpub. Clear golden color. Nice hop aroma in plesent amounts. Big and fresh hop taste from Cascade, Centennial, Columbus and Summit hops. A small but nice caramell taste to balance the hop taste. The bitterness showes up after some time in moderate amounts. Well fermented to give a balanced finnish.

Small lingering white head. Opaque yellow color. No aroma!
Sweet malty taste with low bitterness. Medium body.

Draught at Linden Bru, Berklin.
Bright white head. Nice sparkle in a clear solid yellow color. Small but clean aroma. A tuch of nobel hops. Mild nobel hop taste and a firm bitterness. No sweetness and a god body.

Draught at Linden Bru, Berlin.
Red-brown head. Clear red-brown color.
Hard roasted malt aroma in small amounts. Small but hard roasted malt taste as well. Nice bitterness and a bit thin body.

Draught at Linden Bru, Berlin.
Lasting white head. Clowdy yellow color.A bit of vegetable aroma. Sweet malty taste and a nice bitterness.

Short staying lae. Clear pale yellow color.
Typical mild international lager aroma.
